AimRare Hub v7.1 – Customization & Stability Update

Author: Ben
Version: 7.1
Requires: Executor with Drawing API and HttpGet support

Overview

AimRare Hub v7.1 introduces major improvements in customization, prediction accuracy, performance stability, and aiming logic.
This version expands user control over aimbot behavior, target selection, ESP performance, and color profiles. The update is designed to enhance stability on lower-end devices while offering more advanced configuration options for experienced users.

Key Features
1. Aimbot System

Fully configurable legit-style aim assist

Multi-mode activation: Hold, Toggle, Always-On

Primary and Secondary keybind support

Customizable FOV radius, smoothing, and hit chance

Three prediction models:

Linear

Advanced

High-Precision

Velocity caching with smoothing for improved accuracy

Adjustable prediction curve and prediction speed

Target prioritization:

Closest to crosshair

Lowest distance

Lowest health

Highest threat

Optional wall check and alive check

Optional accessory-ignored raycasting

2. ESP System

Box ESP

Skeleton ESP (R6 & R15)

Name and distance display

Health bar ESP

Team check support

Configurable ESP update rate (30–120 Hz)

FPS-safe skeleton mode (auto-disables skeletons under low FPS)

Multi-color profiles:

Enemy color

Teammate color

Low-health color

Adjustable low-health threshold

3. Fluent UI Integration

AimRare Hub v7.1 uses native Fluent UI components for enhanced interactivity.

Includes:

Toggles, sliders, dropdowns

Keybind controls (primary + secondary bind)

Colorpickers for ESP and FOV circle

Organized tab structure:

Legit Aim

Visuals

Settings

Watermark control

Full unload function removing all Drawing objects and UI

Changelog (v7.1)
Aimbot

Added multi-mode aim activation (Hold, Toggle, Always-On)

Introduced secondary keybind for faster activation

Implemented advanced target prioritization system

Added three prediction models with curve tuning and smoothing

Velocity caching for more realistic motion leading

ESP

ESP rendering is now throttled using a configurable update rate

Added FPS-safe skeleton mode

Introduced color profiles (enemy, teammate, low health)

Added low health threshold settings

Improved visibility caching with optional accessory-ignored raycasts

General

Stability improvements across all modules

Full rewrite of major update loops for consistent timing

Enhanced watermark information (FPS, target, prediction speed)

Performance Improvements

ESP updates now use a fixed time-step loop based on user-configured Hz

Reduced high-frequency raycasting with cached visibility results

Skeleton ESP disabled automatically under low FPS conditions when enabled

Optimized velocity prediction and smoothing logic

Minimized unnecessary Drawing updates

